bilingual.source: There is a label on the outer box.
He stuck on the label to the bottle.
The label won't stay on without glu.
The label was sewn inside the shirt.
bilingual.target: 标签被缝制在衬衫里面。

bilingual.source: Please put a label on each folder.
bilingual.target: 请在每个文件夹上贴上标签。

bilingual.source: There is a label on the top of the box.
bilingual.target: 盒子的上边有一个标签。

bilingual.source: There is a red label on this bottle.

bilingual.source: The label adhered to the bottle perfectly.
bilingual.target: 标签完美地粘附在瓶子上。

list.abstract: LABEL的功能是定义变量或标号的类型，而变量或标号的段属性和偏移属性由该语句所处的位置确定。LABEL是一个符号定义伪指令。
label，英语单词，名词、动词，作名词时意为“标签；商标；绰号；唱片公司；词目标注；（计算机）标记；示踪剂；带垂饰的横带；(Label) （美、法、巴）拉贝尔（人名）”，作动词时意为“贴标签于；把……归类，给……扣帽子；用示踪剂使（物质等）示踪”。

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah. Well, the label promises nutty goodness.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，标签上承诺的是坚果的品质。

yingyinNormal.en: And if you look really close at that label maker label, you'll see a label that says Label.
yingyinNormal.zh: 而且如果你仔细往标签机上的标签看，你会发现有个小小标签写着"标签"。

yingyinNormal.en: Everything in his apartment has a label on it. Including his label maker, which has a label that says Label Maker.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他公寓里所有东西都有标签注明，连他的标签机上都有个标签写着"标签机"。

yingyinNormal.en: You call eight hours alone with my label maker wasted time? Now I'll get to use my shredder!
yingyinNormal.zh: 你是说八小时，加上使用标签机是浪费时间？现在可以用上我的碎纸机了！

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, the label says it is for Peppa and George. Yippee. Look, Mummy. A parcel for George and me. Oh. There's a letter too.
yingyinNormal.zh: 噢，标签上写着是给佩奇和乔治的。太好了！妈妈，你看。乔治和我收到一个包裹。噢。这还有一封信。

yingyinNormal.en: Did it ever occur to you that not everyone has the compulsive need to sort, organize and label the entire world around them? No.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你有没有想过并不是世界上所有的人都有那种强迫症，要把身边的东西都按顺序排好贴上标签？没有。

yingyinNormal.en: Just look at the label of any processed meal, including the drink you wash it down with, and you'll find that corn is in almost everything. And that includes this.
yingyinNormal.zh: 再看看速成食品的标签，还有你喝下的饮料，你会发现玉米无处不在，甚至包括这个。

yingyinNormal.en: Boy, you know, when Sheldon sees you in that dress, he's gonna want to methodically take it off, fold it up, carefully place it in a storage box, label it, and then ravish you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 天啊，谢尔顿看到你穿这条裙子后，一定会想井然有序地把裙子脱掉，折好，小心放入储物盒，贴好标签，然后尽情蹂躏你。

yingyinNormal.en: It cries and laughs and closes its eyes and everything. Santa has given you my doll. No. The label says, "For Suzy Sheep." And Santa has forgotten me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 她可以哭可以笑可以睡觉时闭眼，她什么都能做。圣诞老人把我的礼物给你了。不是的，标签上写着，给小羊苏西。圣诞老人一定是把我给忘了。

yingyinNormal.en: It cries and laughs and closes its eyes and everything. Santa has given you my doll. No. The label says, "For Susie Sheep." And Santa has forgotten me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 她可以哭可以笑可以睡觉时闭眼，她什么都能做。圣诞老人把我的礼物给你了。不是的，标签上写着，给小羊苏西。圣诞老人一定是把我给忘了。

yingyinNormal.en: Distilled into one 95-pound, doe-eyed, bon mot tossing, label-whoring package of girlie evil.
yingyinNormal.zh: 只有95镑，迷人的眼睛，爱搬弄是非，反正能说出一大堆的恶女...

yingyinNormal.en: Well, this is the last box of your clothes. I'm just gonna label it, "What were you thinking?"
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是最后一箱衣服，我会在上面注明 “你在想什么？”

yingyinNormal.en: Every week, the TV Guide comes to Chandler and Joey's apartment. What name appears on the address label?
yingyinNormal.zh: 乔伊和钱德每周都会收到“电视周刊”，请问收件人的姓名为何？

yingyinNormal.en: As many of you know, recently Massimo Corteleoni has agreed to finance the expansion of the James Holt label transforming the work of this visionary artist into a global brand, which is really an exciting enterprise.
yingyinNormal.zh: 正如大部分人所知最近马西莫·科特利让内决定为詹姆斯·浩特这个品牌注资，将这位富于创造灵感的艺术家的作品转变成一个全球品牌，一个振奋人心的产业。

sense_info_list.zh: 标签; 贴条; 标注

examination_example.sentence: According to Cline, mass-market <highlight>labels</highlight> urge consumers to follows improved productivity.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 根据Cline的说法，大众市场的标签敦促消费者关注生产率的提高。

examination_example.sentence: Advances in technology have allowed mass-market <highlight>labels</highlight> to react to trends more quickly and anticipate demand more precisely.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 技术的进步使得大众市场品牌能够更快地对趋势做出反应，更准确地预测需求。

examination_example.sentence: These <highlight>labels</highlight> encourage style-conscious consumers to see clothes as disposable— meant to last only a wash or two.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这些标签鼓励注重风格的消费者将衣服视为一次性的——意味着只能洗一两次。

sense_info_list.en: a classifying phrase or name applied to a person or thing, especially one that is inaccurate or restrictive

examination_example.sentence: Today we have a tendency to <highlight>label</highlight> obesity as a disgrace.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如今，我们有一种把肥胖当做侮辱的倾向。

word_usage.usage:
label既可用作及物动词，也可用作不及物动词，用作及物动词时，可接名词、代词：label+ n./pron.，示例：
The doctor labeled the bottle poison. 
医生在瓶上贴标签，标明有毒。

label可用作双宾语动词：label+ n./pron. + n.，其后还可接as短语充当补足语的复合宾语。示例：
Today we have a tendency to label obesity as a disgrace. 
如今，我们倾向于给肥胖贴上耻辱的标签。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 指附在物品上，标有物品性质、物主、名称、目的地等的标签。其制作材料为纸、亚麻布、金属、塑料等。
指固定在物品上，标明商品的名称、产地和价格等的标签；也可指固定或系在行李等物品上的标签。
